Borrowed from {{bor|en|es|derecho||straight}}, this term seems to have been coined by {{w|Gustavus Detlef Hinrichs}} in 1888 to contrast derechos from tornadoes, which twist<ref>Ray Wolf, [http://www.crh.noaa.gov/dvn/?n=hinrichs "A Brief History of Gustavus Hinrichs, Discoverer of the DERECHO"]</ref><ref>Ammon Shea, [http://blog.oxforddictionaries.com/2012/07/all-about-the-weather/ "All about the weather"], OxfordWords blog, 25 July 2012</ref>; compare the etymology of {{m|en|tornado}}. {{doublet|en|direct}}.

